==English==
===Etymology===
First attested 1656, from [[French]] [[bouillir]] "to boil", from [[Old French]] [[boillir]], from [[Latin]] [[bullīre]], from [[bulla]] "bubble".
===Noun===
#A clear seasoned [[broth]] made by [[simmer]]ing [[beef]] or [[chicken]].
====Synonyms====

*[[broth]]

====Related terms====

*[[bullion]] (bulk gold or silver)

